{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606205","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606205"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:09:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:09:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15898"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15898","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15898"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.61,0.09,0.04,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8589"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72068"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8589","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8589"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15898"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57538"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5323"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10145"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20585"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20586"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72068","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72068"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELabour onset requires complex hormonal signalling between the fetus, placenta and maternal tissues. The fetal adrenal glands play a crucial role in this process.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the endocrine changes that initiate labour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fetal dehydroepiandrosterone is converted to oestrogen by placenta","Fetal adrenal cortex produces cortisol which stimulates prostaglandin synthesis","Fetal anterior pituitary produces dehydroepiandrosterone which is converted by placenta","Placental oestrogen decreases gap junction formation between myometrial cells","Placental oestrogen inhibits prostaglandin production in cervical tissue"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct endocrine pathway involves \u003Cstrong\u003Efetal dehydroepiandrosterone being converted to oestrogen by placental aromatase\u003C/strong\u003E. This increased oestrogen has several important effects on labour initiation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFetal adrenal cortex produces cortisol\u003C/strong\u003E - While cortisol is important for fetal lung maturation, it is not directly involved in labour initiation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFetal anterior pituitary produces dehydroepiandrosterone\u003C/strong\u003E - Dehydroepiandrosterone is produced by the adrenal cortex, not the anterior pituitary\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlacental oestrogen decreases gap junction formation\u003C/strong\u003E - Oestrogen actually increases gap junctions between myometrial cells, enabling coordinated contractions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlacental oestrogen inhibits prostaglandin production\u003C/strong\u003E - Oestrogen stimulates prostaglandin production, which promotes cervical ripening\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe conversion of dehydroepiandrosterone to oestrogen represents a key example of fetal-placental cooperation in triggering labour onset.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The fetal adrenal cortex produces dehydroepiandrosterone which is converted to oestrogen by the placenta","Oestrogen increases gap junctions between myometrial cells to enable coordinated uterine contractions","Oestrogen increases prostaglandin production which promotes cervical ripening"],"references":["Zhang J, Merialdi M, Platt LD, Kramer MS. Defining normal and abnormal fetal growth: promises and challenges. Am J Obstet Gynecol. 2010 Jun;202(6):522-8. doi: 10.1016/j.ajog.2009.10.889. Epub 2010 Jan 13. PMID: 20074690; PMCID: PMC2878887.","Napso T, Yong HEJ, Lopez-Tello J, Sferruzzi-Perri AN. The Role of Placental Hormones in Mediating Maternal Adaptations to Support Pregnancy and Lactation. Front Physiol. 2018 Aug 17;9:1091. doi: 10.3389/fphys.2018.01091. PMID: 30174608; PMCID: PMC6108594","Newbern D, Freemark M. Placental hormones and the control of maternal metabolism and fetal growth. Curr Opin Endocrinol Diabetes Obes. 2011 Dec;18(6):409-16. doi: 10.1097/MED.0b013e32834c800d. PMID: 21986512","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57538"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15898"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57538","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57538"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:14:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:14:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8589"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72068"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"update